author: hansweltar
commit_message:
Remove infinite loop when js ends with comment

Fixes Issue #1
To reproduce: jsmin.jsmin("//test\r\n") This will hang indefinately.

We remove the empty string as a valid newline character when eating up
comments. The empty string is namely used as EOF marker and the code should
stop when it reads ''.

We also added a unittest for this case.

author: Gennady Kovshenin
commit_message:
{/.. is not considered to be in_re

See issue #1, but basically since `{\` does not trigger `in_re`, a `\\`
chain inside the regular expression literal will be interpreted as a
one line comment and removed completely (test case `{/\//}` which
results in a minified syntax error due to mismatched bracket when it's
turned into `{/\` (single line comment removed).

Not sure if this breaks anything but all tests pass.
